$SPY $QQQ $VIX $AAPL Now… I can’t stress this enough… bulls aren’t out of the woods yet. We still have AAPL and AMZN reporting after hours on Thursday. And we have the FOMC federal funds rate decision next week May 4, 2pm. So as long as Apple and Amazons earnings are on par with what MSFT delivered (which I believe it will be) and the FED shows a 50 basis point rate hike THEN THE VIX MELTS AND THE MARKET ROARS HIGHER. Tomorrow could be a red day… Thursdays usually have low volume and the day before big earnings always creates an elevated VIX. Friday could be nice day. (speculating on exact movement on a specific day is a fools errand by the way but nevertheless I’m entertaining it) That brings the game plan towards Monday and Tuesday pre Fed meeting. This is where the fear machine will crank up again and you could have a possibly another selloff going into the meeting out of fear. Be advised. After meeting (if it is indeed a 50 BPS hike) we moon.
